Tango Discographies

This is a prototype version of a webpage that some time might come to life in the future. For comments or feedback you can write me at tango-discoeat this spambot@and this tooposteo.de

Introduction

Dear visitior,

this page is concerned with recorded Tango music roughly in the period from 1930 till 1955 and collects discographical information of the most poular dance orchestras of that time. There are already several projects like tango.info, tango-dj.at, todotango.comor milonga.co.uk, which all collect and present large amounts of information about tango recordings, the orchestras, composers and, importantly, about the reissues of this music on LP, CD or in digital format.

This webpage will not add much new to this. The mentioned projects and databases are excellent for finding specific information around single recordings, their republications or other recordings of the same composition. However, this detailedness can at times make it difficult to grasp the bigger picture and to get an overwiew of the entirety of avaliable recordings from an orchestra or to see the evolution of its recordings over time. This is what this page wants to adress by presenting extensive and hopefully complete listings of the recordings made by the big orchestras in a way thats convenient to browse, filter, and search.

Lucio Demare

Juan D’Arienzo

Juan D'Arienzo made his first recordings in the years 1928/29 before he became hugely popular from 1935 onwards. From that time he was continiously recording till 1975. The early recordings and the time from 1955 onwards are not yet covered here. For intresting comments and further information make sure to have a look at the gread Juan D'Arienzo Discography at Tangoteca.
